One of the most usefull and used data structure in computer science,
when it comes to modeling in real life

In short a graph is simply a set of values that are related in a
pairwise fashion

Each item in a graph it's called a node or a vertex.

Nodes are connected with edges

Graphs are great data structures to model real world relationships representing links

link graphs are ideal when you are working with things that connect to other things

like the internet, friendships, family, roads (one city to another)

Amazon uses it for their recommendation engines
Google Maps for determining the shortest path to where you wanna go

Graphs are good to relationships
